WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.667
(gentle music)

00:00:32.800 --> 00:00:37.092
- [Voiceover] Several
grains of the ancient world

00:00:37.625 --> 00:00:39.208
are recently making a comeback

00:00:39.375 --> 00:00:41.041
due to modern man's pursuit

00:00:41.208 --> 00:00:42.667
of a healthier lifestyle.

00:00:42.834 --> 00:00:44.999
Quinoa, amaranth, spelt,

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:47.208
some of the grains
that flourished

00:00:47.375 --> 00:00:49.041
during the early civilization,

00:00:49.208 --> 00:00:50.999
and yet perished as
the world entered

00:00:51.125 --> 00:00:53.375
the modern era.

00:00:53.542 --> 00:00:55.125
But if there is one
ancient grain that can

00:00:56.709 --> 00:00:58.500
personify immortality,

00:00:58.667 --> 00:01:00.709
that would be maize.

00:01:00.875 --> 00:01:02.583
Belonging to the grass
tribe Andropogonae,

00:01:05.083 --> 00:01:08.041
of the family gramineae,

00:01:08.208 --> 00:01:09.792
maize or zea maize, is
believed to have been

00:01:09.959 --> 00:01:12.999
cultivated first in Mesoamerica,

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:15.583
in 2100 BC.

00:01:15.750 --> 00:01:17.709
The Mayan civilization,

00:01:19.375 --> 00:01:20.999
one of the greatest
early civilizations

00:01:20.999 --> 00:01:22.999
in America and in the world,

00:01:23.083 --> 00:01:25.125
was primarily based on maize.

00:01:25.291 --> 00:01:28.291
The Mayans were
great agriculturists.

00:01:28.458 --> 00:01:30.999
They were not only
known for their

00:01:30.999 --> 00:01:32.667
sophisticated irrigation system,

00:01:32.834 --> 00:01:35.000
but also for the advanced
cultivating techniques

00:01:35.166 --> 00:01:37.999
they used to develop
maize from a wild variety

00:01:37.999 --> 00:01:40.792
of grass called teosinte.

00:01:40.959 --> 00:01:43.125
For some time, maize's
true origin was a mystery

00:01:44.834 --> 00:01:47.750
for botanists, archaeologists,

00:01:47.917 --> 00:01:49.999
historians, and
even geneticists.

00:01:49.999 --> 00:01:53.792
Many questioned if
teosinte is maize's

00:01:53.959 --> 00:01:56.166
true ancestor, due to
their dissimilarities.

00:01:56.333 --> 00:01:59.999
Until in 1932, American
Nobel Prize winner,

00:01:59.999 --> 00:02:04.375
George Beadle of
Cornell University

00:02:04.542 --> 00:02:06.959
conducted researches
and experiments

00:02:06.999 --> 00:02:09.208
that scientifically
validated that maize

00:02:09.375 --> 00:02:11.999
and teosinte share
similar chromosomes,

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:14.999
and that they came
from the same specie.

00:02:15.125 --> 00:02:17.542
In a more recent study,

00:02:19.625 --> 00:02:21.333
botanist John Doebley of
the University of Wisconsin,

00:02:21.500 --> 00:02:24.792
was able to identify
maize's paternity.

00:02:24.959 --> 00:02:27.583
By comparing DNA
profiles of teosinte

00:02:29.542 --> 00:02:32.000
from various
geographical locations

00:02:32.166 --> 00:02:34.333
and different
varieties of maize,

00:02:34.500 --> 00:02:36.667
he found out that maize
and the teosinte found

00:02:36.834 --> 00:02:39.291
in central Balsas River
Valley of southern Mexico,

00:02:39.458 --> 00:02:42.999
were the most
genetically similar.

00:02:42.999 --> 00:02:45.959
So, he postulated
that central Balsas

00:02:45.999 --> 00:02:48.625
is the cradle of
maize evolution,

00:02:48.792 --> 00:02:51.417
and estimated that
domestication occurred

00:02:51.583 --> 00:02:53.834
about 9,000 years ago.

00:02:53.999 --> 00:02:56.083
Maize is a very adaptable plant

00:02:58.625 --> 00:03:00.875
since it can grow in
almost any type of soil,

00:03:00.999 --> 00:03:03.750
except in soils
with high salinity.

00:03:03.917 --> 00:03:06.999
And depending on the variety,

00:03:06.999 --> 00:03:08.417
soil and climate conditions,

00:03:08.583 --> 00:03:10.333
growing maize can
take as little as

00:03:10.500 --> 00:03:12.375
60 days, or as long as 120 days.

00:03:12.542 --> 00:03:15.917
It's a very tall
plant that grows up to

00:03:17.417 --> 00:03:19.625
an average height of eight feet.

00:03:19.792 --> 00:03:22.208
Its singular stem is
physically similar

00:03:22.375 --> 00:03:24.625
to that of a bamboo cane.

00:03:24.792 --> 00:03:26.583
With an average of 20
alternating internodes,

00:03:26.750 --> 00:03:29.417
and from each node, a
leaf sprouts with an

00:03:29.583 --> 00:03:32.000
average length of four feet.

00:03:32.166 --> 00:03:34.999
It grows a tassel on
its top most part,

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:37.333
which can release
millions of grains,

00:03:37.500 --> 00:03:39.875
and is responsible
for producing pollen

00:03:39.999 --> 00:03:41.999
that can fertilize
the cob or ear.

00:03:42.041 --> 00:03:44.750
A cob is usually 15
to 39 centimeters long

00:03:45.917 --> 00:03:48.999
and can have up to 800 kernels.

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:51.333
Yellow is the most
famous color of maize.

00:03:53.667 --> 00:03:56.458
However, due to
hybridization there are

00:03:56.625 --> 00:03:58.999
over 60 varieties of this grain

00:03:58.999 --> 00:04:01.208
in the market today,

00:04:01.375 --> 00:04:02.834
and it comes in different colors

00:04:02.999 --> 00:04:04.792
such as red, pink, black,

00:04:04.959 --> 00:04:07.375
blue, and purple.

00:04:07.542 --> 00:04:09.999
Each variety has
its specific use,

00:04:10.083 --> 00:04:12.125
and it reaches the market
in a specific form.

00:04:12.291 --> 00:04:15.375
For example, the
variety saccharata,

00:04:15.542 --> 00:04:18.999
or rugosa, cultivated
to have young ears

00:04:18.999 --> 00:04:21.999
and more sugar than
other varieties,

00:04:21.999 --> 00:04:24.083
is known in the market
at "sweet corn".

00:04:24.250 --> 00:04:27.917
The variety, amylacea,

00:04:27.999 --> 00:04:30.208
grown to have starchy kernels,

00:04:30.375 --> 00:04:32.458
is processed into what
we know as corn flower.

00:04:32.625 --> 00:04:36.250
The variety everta,

00:04:36.417 --> 00:04:38.208
arrives in the
market as popcorn.

00:04:38.375 --> 00:04:40.999
And the variety
called indentata,

00:04:40.999 --> 00:04:43.333
is mostly grown
as livestock feed,

00:04:43.500 --> 00:04:45.999
and is an ingredient in
some industrial products.

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:49.166
It's simply fascinating
how a grain can

00:04:54.375 --> 00:04:56.709
withstand the test
of time and history,

00:04:56.875 --> 00:04:59.083
and remain invaluable
and indispensable today,

00:04:59.250 --> 00:05:01.999
as it did thousands
of years ago.

00:05:02.083 --> 00:05:05.125
(gentle music)

00:05:09.999 --> 00:05:12.542
(upbeat music)

00:05:17.750 --> 00:05:20.917
The ancient grain maize,

00:05:37.792 --> 00:05:39.250
has provided the
Mayan civilization

00:05:39.417 --> 00:05:41.667
a great service of
feeding and nourishing

00:05:41.834 --> 00:05:43.999
its people, physically
and spiritually.

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:46.999
Aside from its religious roles,

00:05:49.250 --> 00:05:50.999
its nutrient profile
is also responsible

00:05:51.083 --> 00:05:53.709
for allowing the Mayans,
and other indigenous

00:05:53.875 --> 00:05:55.999
Americans enjoy healthy lives.

00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:58.999
Maize's high fiber content
makes it beneficial

00:06:01.250 --> 00:06:03.999
to people who are at
risk of heart diseases,

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:06.792
due to its cholesterol
reducing capabilities.

00:06:06.959 --> 00:06:10.709
The soluble fiber of
maize binds itself

00:06:10.875 --> 00:06:12.999
with cholesterol and
excretes it naturally,

00:06:13.083 --> 00:06:16.333
thus preventing the body
from absorbing it further.

00:06:16.500 --> 00:06:19.999
Meanwhile, the
insoluble fiber of maize

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:22.709
removes toxins from
the digestive tract.

00:06:22.875 --> 00:06:25.999
It absorbs water
which softens stools

00:06:26.125 --> 00:06:28.500
for easier and more
regular bowel movements.

00:06:28.667 --> 00:06:31.333
Since it prevents constipation,

00:06:33.250 --> 00:06:35.083
promotes a cleaner and
healthier digestive system,

00:06:35.250 --> 00:06:37.875
it reduces the risk
of colon cancer.

00:06:37.999 --> 00:06:40.999
Maize has more
vitamin A compared

00:06:42.999 --> 00:06:45.000
to other grains.

00:06:45.166 --> 00:06:47.000
It has beta crypto-xanthin,

00:06:47.166 --> 00:06:48.999
a phytonutrient,
converted into vitamin A,

00:06:49.041 --> 00:06:52.125
and is believed to
have anti-inflammatory

00:06:52.291 --> 00:06:54.542
properties that
can benefit people

00:06:54.709 --> 00:06:56.999
with rheumatic arthritis.

00:06:57.125 --> 00:06:59.333
It can also provide
B vitamins, thiamin,

00:06:59.500 --> 00:07:01.999
niacin, and folate, which
promote healthy nerves,

00:07:02.041 --> 00:07:05.834
and cognitive functions.

00:07:05.999 --> 00:07:08.000
These also aid the
body's natural metabolism

00:07:08.166 --> 00:07:10.709
process by facilitating
the conversion

00:07:10.875 --> 00:07:13.333
of carbohydrates into energy.

00:07:13.500 --> 00:07:16.667
Folic acid deficiency
is common among pregnant

00:07:16.834 --> 00:07:19.458
women, so eating maize
may keep them and

00:07:19.625 --> 00:07:22.542
their babies nourished
throughout the pregnancy.

00:07:22.709 --> 00:07:26.583
Potassium,
phosphorous, megnesium

00:07:26.750 --> 00:07:29.083
are maizes top three minerals,

00:07:29.250 --> 00:07:31.375
which are all crucial in
maintaining bone health.

00:07:31.542 --> 00:07:34.417
In addition, magnesium
also contributes

00:07:34.583 --> 00:07:37.208
in regulating heart rate.

00:07:37.375 --> 00:07:39.999
Maize also contains
various anti-oxidants,

00:07:40.041 --> 00:07:42.999
and phytonutrients.

00:07:42.999 --> 00:07:44.999
However, presence and amounts

00:07:45.041 --> 00:07:46.834
depend on the variety.

00:07:46.999 --> 00:07:48.709
For example, yellow
corn is rich in

00:07:50.625 --> 00:07:52.583
carotenoids, lutein,
and zeaxanthin.

00:07:52.750 --> 00:07:55.999
Blue corn has a high
anthocyanin content.

00:07:58.083 --> 00:08:01.083
And purple corn contains
protocatechuic acid.

00:08:02.583 --> 00:08:06.000
Other phytonutrients
found in maize are

00:08:08.375 --> 00:08:10.792
ferulic acid, beta-carotene,

00:08:10.959 --> 00:08:13.999
vanillic acid, coumaric acid,

00:08:14.125 --> 00:08:17.834
caffeic acid, and syringic acid.

00:08:17.999 --> 00:08:21.709
To fully appreciate
its nutritional value,

00:08:25.625 --> 00:08:28.291
here's how much 100
grams of maize can

00:08:28.458 --> 00:08:30.999
contribute to a person's
daily requirement

00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:33.709
of nutrients,
minerals, and vitamins.

00:08:33.875 --> 00:08:36.417
100 grams of maize can
provide a person with

00:08:39.375 --> 00:08:41.999
eleven percent of
his daily requirement

00:08:42.125 --> 00:08:44.166
of dietary fiber,
six percent of his

00:08:44.333 --> 00:08:47.083
protein and carbohydrate
requirements,

00:08:47.250 --> 00:08:49.999
and four percent of his
calorie requirement.

00:08:49.999 --> 00:08:53.083
For a person's daily
requirement of mineral intake,

00:08:56.000 --> 00:08:59.000
100 grams of maize can provide

00:08:59.166 --> 00:09:01.208
nine percent magnesium,
nine percent phosphorous,

00:09:01.375 --> 00:09:04.999
eight percent potassium,

00:09:05.041 --> 00:09:06.750
and eight percent manganese.

00:09:06.917 --> 00:09:09.125
Intake of 100 grams
of maize also provides

00:09:12.875 --> 00:09:15.542
thirteen percent of the
daily required thiamin,

00:09:15.709 --> 00:09:19.500
eleven percent of the
daily required Vitamin C

00:09:19.667 --> 00:09:22.208
and folate, and
nine percent of the

00:09:22.375 --> 00:09:25.041
daily required niacin.

00:09:25.208 --> 00:09:27.333
Good thing maize comes
in varying forms,

00:09:32.542 --> 00:09:34.999
so it can be enjoyed
in numerous ways.

00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:37.667
Whether it's consumed
as an ingredient

00:09:40.999 --> 00:09:42.875
in baked goods, as
a morning cereal,

00:09:42.999 --> 00:09:45.166
or straight from the cob,

00:09:45.333 --> 00:09:47.291
maize is undeniably
one of nature's

00:09:47.458 --> 00:09:49.250
greatest gifts to mankind.

00:09:49.417 --> 00:09:51.999
